<paragraph id="964A0933C100FFE926A6F30F78FAFACA" blockId="0.[151,1437,1243,1619]" box="[199,427,1379,1403]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">
Distribution: 
<collectingCountry id="EEE249A3C100FFE92737F30F78F9FACA" box="[342,424,1379,1403]" name="Taiwan" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="964A0933C100FFE926A6F3E47B64F9E2" blockId="0.[151,1437,1243,1619]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">
Notes. This species was described by Wileman (1915) on the basis of 
<specimenCount id="80F3C2BAC100FFE925C4F3E47D56FA2E" box="[933,1031,1415,1439]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" type="male">two male</specimenCount>
<typeStatus id="494EB791C100FFE9226DF3E47D38FA11" box="[1036,1129,1416,1440]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">syntypes</typeStatus>
from Kanshirei [Guanziling, 
<collectingRegion id="5431C7D1C100FFE926F6F3C779B3FA72" box="[151,226,1451,1475]" country="Taiwan" name="Tainan" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Tainan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="EEE249A3C100FFE9268FF3C77813FA72" box="[238,322,1451,1475]" name="Taiwan" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
]. 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C100FFE92732F3C078B1FA72" author="Wang, H. Y." box="[339,480,1451,1476]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" refId="ref4025" refString="Wang, H. Y. (1994) Noctuidae. Guide book to Insects in Taiwan 8. Shu Shin Books, Taipei, 477 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1994">Wang (1994)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated 
<specimenCount id="80F3C2BAC100FFE9243BF3C07B8EFA75" box="[602,735,1452,1476]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">one syntype</specimenCount>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C100FFE9248BF3C77ABBFA72" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[746,1002,1451,1475]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref3670" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2014 a) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of the genus Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 1. Taxonomic notes and description of 28 new species from Asia. Oriental Insects, 48 (1 - 2), 1 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.2014.959790" type="journal article" year="2014">Tóth &amp; Ronkay (2014a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 55) illustrated the female genitalia, but they did not show any evidence of the identification of this species. Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C100FFE92259F3A37C3CFA56" author="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[1080,1389,1487,1511]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" pagination="253 - 262" refId="ref3886" refString="Toth, B. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2015 b) Revision of the Palaearctic and Oriental species of Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae). Part 4. Description of nine new species. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 18 (2), 253 - 262. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. aspen. 2015.02.001" type="journal article" year="2015">Tóth &amp; Ronkay (2015b: 254</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 6) illustrated the male specimen without abdomen with caption “ 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C100FFE92532F39F7DD1F9BA" authority="Wileman" authorityName="Wileman" authorityYear="1915" box="[851,1152,1523,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochronota">
<emphasis id="A481D521C100FFE92532F39F7D49F9BA" box="[851,1048,1523,1547]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">Naarda ochronota</emphasis>
Wileman
</taxonomicName>
male, 
<typeStatus id="494EB791C100FFE922A8F39F7C7AF9BA" box="[1225,1323,1523,1547]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">holotype</typeStatus>
”, however this specimen should be 
<typeStatus id="494EB791C100FFE927F8F07478BDF981" box="[409,492,1560,1584]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">syntype</typeStatus>
rather than 
<typeStatus id="494EB791C100FFE92408F07B7B9BF99E" box="[617,714,1559,1583]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">holotype</typeStatus>
. In the same study, they also examined the other 
<typeStatus id="494EB791C100FFE922ABF0747C4CF981" box="[1226,1309,1560,1584]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591">syntype</typeStatus>
(“topotypic male specimen—BM Noct. 21786 
<specimenCount id="80F3C2BAC100FFE9246DF0577B4EF9E2" box="[524,543,1595,1619]" pageId="0" pageNumber="591" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
”).
</paragraph>
